{"description": "By default, the SELinux boolean <tt>pppd_for_user</tt> is disabled.\nIf this setting is enabled, it should be disabled.\n\nTo disable the <code>pppd_for_user</code> SELinux boolean, run the following command:\n<pre>$ sudo setsebool -P pppd_for_user off</pre>", "rationale": "", "severity": "medium", "references": {}, "control_references": {}, "components": ["selinux"], "identifiers": {}, "ocil_clause": "pppd_for_user is not disabled", "ocil": "\nRun the following command to determine if the <code>pppd_for_user</code> SELinux boolean is disabled:\n<pre>$ getsebool pppd_for_user</pre>\nIf properly configured, the output should show the following:\n<code>pppd_for_user --> off</code>", "oval_external_content": null, "fixtext": "", "checktext": "", "vuldiscussion": "", "srg_requirement": "", "warnings": [], "conflicts": [], "requires": [], "policy_specific_content": {}, "platform": null, "platforms": [], "sce_metadata": {"check-import": "stdout", "check-export": ["var_pppd_for_user=xccdf_org.ssgproject.content_value_var_pppd_for_user"], "platform": ["multi_platform_all"], "environment": "any", "filename": "sebool_pppd_for_user.sh", "relative_path": "rhel9/checks/sce/sebool_pppd_for_user.sh"}, "inherited_platforms": ["system_with_kernel", "selinux or bootc or osbuild"], "cpe_platform_names": [], "inherited_cpe_platform_names": ["bootc_or_osbuild_or_selinux", "system_with_kernel"], "bash_conditional": null, "fixes": {}, "check_type": null, "inputs": [], "expression": null, "failure_reason": null, "title": "Disable the pppd_for_user SELinux Boolean", "definition_location": "/home/greek_fire/.git/content/linux_os/guide/system/selinux/selinux-booleans/sebool_pppd_for_user/rule.yml", "template": {"name": "sebool", "vars": {"seboolid": "pppd_for_user"}, "backends": {}}}